      <h2 class="h1 best-practice__header">Referring someone in need of help</h2>

      <h2 class="h2">Manchester city council</h2>

      <p>During the day, referrals into this accommodation can be made via:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The Council Rough Sleeper team - <em>0161 234 5339</em> or <a href="mailto:roughsleepersteam@manchester.gov.uk">roughsleepersteam@manchester.gov.uk</a></li>
        <li>For over 25s: <a href="/find-help/organisation/?organisation=booth-centre">Booth Centre</a></li>
        <li>For under 25s: <a href="/find-help/organisation/?organisation=ypsf">Centrepoint North</a></li>
        <!--<li><a href="/find-help/organisation/?organisation=riverside">Riversideâ€˜s outreach service</a>.</li>-->
      </ul>

      <p>When daytime services are closed you can refer through:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>MCC out of hours number on <em>0161 234 5001</em></li>
        <!--<li>Referral centre 52 Oldham St, M4 1LE 9pm-1am</li>-->
        <!--<li><a href="/find-help/organisation/?organisation=coffee4craig">Coffee4Craig</a>: 8pm-midnight on <em>07749598136</em></li>-->
      </ul>

      <h2 class="h2">Bolton council</h2>

      <p>During the day, ring Bolton Town Hall on 01204 333333. Out of hours you can refer via the duty social worker 01204 337777.</p>

      <h2 class="h2">Tameside council</h2>

      <p>To establish whether or not emergency provision is available in Tameside, ring Tameside Housing Advice on 0161 331 2700 between 9am-3pm, or out of hours 0161 331 2700/2888. They will make the accommodation placement on a night by night basis and ask the person to return the next day. If the weather is forecast to below zero degrees Celsius the next night the accommodation will be rebooked.</p>

      <h2 class="h2">Other GM councils</h2>

      <p>For all other Greater Manchester regions, contact your local council or housing options team for advice.</p>

